**Background:** This project wraps pflag and cobra so that very little of these
libraries are visible or usable on the seam.

We accept an "app ID" through a YAML file that we use to determine custom
application folders on the host OS system. Different systems use different
structures for this though; macOS uses reverse-DNS names like `com.example.foo`,
whereas Windows normally throws just an application name, and Linux frequently
uses a lowercase system name.

## Goal

Align the `app-id` so it's configurable for different systems.

### Implementation

Currently we just have `app-id: "string"`

The new plan is to make this `app-id: "string"` as a default for all, OR

```yaml
app-id:
  default: fallback-for-any-system
  macos: mac-id
  windows: windows-id
  ...
```

Do this in the following way:

* Update the schema so that the `app-id` field is its own type, something like

  ```go
  type HostOS string
  const (
    HostOSDefault HostOS = "default"
    HostOSWindows HostOS = "windows"
    ...
  )
  func (os *HostOS) UnmarshalText(s []byte) error { ... }

  type AppID map[HostOS]string

  func (id AppID) For(goos string) string { /* ... */ }
  ```

* This is going to require a custom `yaml.Unmarshaler` implementation so that
  `AppID` is capable of unmarshaling from either a string, in which case it's
  equivalent to setting `default: <value>`, or from a map.

* When deciding the AppID for storage construction, leverage this configuration
  and pass in the GOOS value.

